  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Recurrence of uveitis before and after implantation. Postimplantation recurrences were evaluated using protocol-defined criteria based upon changes in VA, vitreous haze, and the presence of cells in the anterior chamber of the eye.</measure>
    <time_frame>1 year pre-implantation; 3 years post-implantation</time_frame>
  </primary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>Between-dose group and within-subject comparisons (Study to Fellow eye) for uveitis recurrence; time to first recurrence; need for adjunctive uveitis treatment; reduction in the area of cystoid macular edema; results of quality of life surveys.</measure>
    <time_frame>1 year pre-implantation; 3 years post-implantation</time_frame>
  </secondary_outcome>
